      "message": "ok, i found it: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/grpc/prpc/encoding.go;l\u003d151?q\u003dunwrap%20f:prpc%2Fencoding.go\u0026sq\u003d\n\ncurrent code happens to work because we don\u0027t use Attachf (except here which happens to use the code INTERNAL which is the default interpretation). In a more advanced case that we will have at some point, we will want to use appstatus.Attachf on an existing non-status error. Then this code will break.\nappstatus.Errorf happens to work because its impl is 1) create a true status error 2) call Attachf on it.\n\nFWIW it is not great that prpc does this. Maybe it shouldn\u0027t.",
